'''Coffins''' can be found on all floors of the [[Hallowed Sepulchre]] and they require {{SCP|Thieving|66|link=yes}} {{Boostable|yes}}, granting 200 experience when successfully looted. The player will need to pass a [[Hallowed Sepulchre#Requirements|skilling challenge]] and there must be time left before they can attempt to loot it. Occasionally when failing to loot the coffin, the player will be [[poison]]ed.

The [[strange old lockpick]] has an increased success chance at opening a coffin when compared to the standard [[lockpick]]. It will not use any charges to do this.{{CiteReddit|author=Mod Husky|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/2007scape/comments/gzrpvi/problems_with_the_hallowed_sepulchre/fthzut1|title=Darkmeyer Improvements|quote=did you know that the strange old lockpick already has a higher success rate than a normal one, you can still fail but it's a bit lower|date=9 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/BFTpp|archivedate=13 June 2020}}

Coffins will always give the player [[hallowed mark]]s. The number received depends on which floor the coffin is looted on.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Husky|url=https://twitter.com/JagexHusky/status/1273653084334493696|date=18 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/j7M8F|archivedate=18 June 2020|quote=Well, it's my birthday tomorrow and scuffed flames appear to be fixed so I'm in a good mood. As a result here's the ever so requested droprates from the sepulchre put together nicely on these images by @JagexRy}}

